The line parallel to 
                              \Vect{u}
                            through 
                              (2,1,2)
                            intersects the line 
                              t \Vect{v}
                            at 
                              1 \cdot \Vect{v}
                           .

The line parallel to 
                              \Vect{v}
                            through 
                              (2,1,2)
                            intersects the line 
                              s \Vect{u}
                            at 
                              2 \cdot \Vect{u}
                           .

Therefore 
                              \Vect{x} = 2 \Vect{u} + \Vect{v}
                           .

