A linear combination of 
                        \Vect{x}
                      is a vector of the form 
                        t\cdot \Vect{x}
                     , where 
                        t
                      is in 
                        \RNr
                     . This means that a linear combination of 
                        \Vect{x}
                      is any vector which is parallel to 
                        \Vect{x}
                      or, in other words, which lies on the line in the direction of 
                        \Vect{x}
                     .

